12 APPROPRIATIONS TO IMPLEMENT PART I
13 SECTION 1.2.(a) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department
14 of Health and Human Services, Division of Public Health, the sum of five million dollars
15 ($5,000,000) in recurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be used and
16 allocated as follows:
17 (1) Ninety-three thousand five hundred thirteen dollars ($93,513) in recurring
18 funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to establish a full-time,
19 permanent Public Health Program Coordinator IV position within the
20 Department of Health and Human Services dedicated to performing the
21 following duties:
22 a. Providing application assistance to Maternal Care Access Grant
23 Program applicants.
24 b. Providing technical assistance to Maternal Care Access Grant Program
25 recipients.
26 c. Preparing the reports due under Section 1.1(f) of this Part.
27 (2) Four million nine hundred six thousand four hundred eighty-seven dollars
28 ($4,906,487) in recurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal
29 biennium to be allocated to the Maternal Care Access Grant Program
30 authorized by Section 1.1 of this Part. The Department of Health and Human
31 Services may use up to one percent (1%) of these funds for administrative
32 purposes related to the grant program. The balance of these funds shall be used
33 to operate the grant program.
34 SECTION 1.2.(b) The Department of Health and Human Services is authorized to
35 hire one full-time, permanent Public Health Program Coordinator IV position to perform the
36 duties described in subsection (a) of this section.
37 SECTION 1.3. This Part becomes effective July 1, 2025.
