29 PART IV. PERINATAL EDUCATION GRANT PROGRAM
30 SECTION 4.1.(a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
31 (1) Department. – The North Carolina Department of Health and Human
32 Services.
33 (2) Perinatal education program. – A program that operates for the primary
34 purpose of educating pregnant women and their families about healthy
35 pregnancy, preparation for labor and birth, breast feeding, newborn care, or
36 any combination of these.
37 SECTION 4.1.(b) Establishment of Grant Program. – The Department shall
38 establish and administer a Perinatal Education Grant Program to award competitive grants to
39 eligible entities to establish or expand perinatal education programs in rural, underserved, or
40 low-wealth areas of the State. The Department shall establish eligibility requirements for
41 program participation which shall, at a minimum, require that applicants be community-based
42 organizations that offer perinatal education and resources aligned with evidence-based practices
43 for improving maternal health outcomes for black women.
44 SECTION 4.1.(c) Outreach and Application Assistance. – Beginning September 1,
45 2025, the Department shall (i) conduct outreach to encourage eligible applicants to apply for
46 grants under this program and (ii) provide application assistance to eligible applicants on best
47 practices for applying for grants under this program. In conducting the outreach required by this
48 section, the Department shall give special consideration to eligible applicants that meet the
49 following criteria:
