34 PART V. MOMNI-BUS INITIATIVE
35 SECTION 5.1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
36 Health and Human Services, Division of Public Health (DPH), the sum of six million five
37 hundred thousand dollars ($6,500,000) for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to create
38 a Momni-Bus Initiative. The purpose of the Momni-Bus Initiative is to fund efforts to expand
39 access to maternal and infant health care and parenting programs, supports, and services to
40 families residing in geographic areas of the State where there is limited or no access to maternity
41 care services, including obstetric providers, a hospital or birth center, prenatal care, or postpartum
42 care. As part of this initiative, the Department shall allocate and use the funds appropriated by
43 this section as follows:
44 (1) One million five hundred thousand dollars ($1,500,000) to provide a directed
45 grant to the March of Dimes, Inc., a nonprofit corporation in North Carolina,
46 to support its work toward ending preventable maternal health risks and
47 deaths, ending preventable preterm birth and infant death, and closing the
48 health equity gap.
49 (2) Five million dollars ($5,000,000) to award directed grants on a competitive
50 basis to nonprofit, community-based, and faith-based organizations that offer
51 programs, supports, and services aligned with evidence-based practices for a
House Bill 725-First Edition Page 9

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 healthy pregnancy through the postpartum period, infant health and care, and
2 parenting programs, supports, and services. The DPH shall establish an
3 application process and eligibility criteria for awarding the grants authorized
4 under this subdivision. By October 1, 2027, and October 1, 2028, the DPH
5 shall submit a report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health
6 and Human Services and the Fiscal Research Division on grants awarded
7 under this subdivision. The report shall include at least all of the following:
8 a. The identity and a brief description of the community health activities
9 performed by each grantee.
10 b. The amount of funding awarded to each grantee.
11 c. The number of persons served by each grantee.
12 SECTION 5.2. This Part becomes effective July 1, 2025.
